      <ModernPractice id="ritualModernPractice">
         <ab><bibl>Redard and Daruwalla, 2021</bibl>, p. 89:</ab>
         <ab class="ab_indent">"As above, while reciting <em>imǝm haomǝm</em> for the second time, the chief priest, taking the libation wire again, dipping it in the milk saucer, while wetting the
            date-palm leaf of the bundle, he recites. And at the start of the dedication, the chief priest puts the libation wire back on the milk saucer."</ab>
      </ModernPractice>
